  <body>
    <p>On a general note,  authors describing bioinformatics tools should consider to provide web assess at least to a demo version of their software, for testing by reviewers and potential users alike.</p>
    <p> Overall, the manuscript is interesting and clearly written. </p>
    <p> Major issues</p>
    <p> ------------</p>
    <p> 1. In my opinion, it's a serious shortcoming that MarkerScan doesn't verify the assumed taxonomy of the target species (p.7).</p>
    <p> 2. MarkerScan reports contaminant bacterial species (p.9), but no evidence is provided that the 'detected bacterial sequences' are indeed in the sample.</p>
    <p> Minor points</p>
    <p> -------------</p>
    <p> Methods - Workflow</p>
    <p> - Please clarify in how far the workflow depends on the PacBio technology, and if the other long-read technologies are also supported.</p>
    <p> p.4 left col. </p>
    <p> - "The putative SSU sequences are extracted.."  Does 'sequences' mean 'reads'? Clarify.</p>
    <p> - "For every observed family, all publicly available genomes". Clarify: genomes from ALL species of a given family?</p>
    <p> Result section:</p>
    <p> - The headers in the Results should more explicitly state the subsections' content. The first subsection seems to compare binning while the second deals with taxonomic assignment. Without such clarification, the selection of the tools benchmarked later appears arbitrary.</p>
    <p> p.7</p>
    <p> - Justify why MarkerScan was not compared to e.g., Concoct, which has higher F1 scores in Fig. 2C.</p>
    <p> - Spell out INSDC</p>
    <p> - "Mythimna impura. A more complex issue arises, when..contaminated..." Please rephrase, because 'eukaryotic contamination' is not specific to M. impura, but was already an issue in the weevil example.</p>
    <p> Fig. 3. </p>
    <p> - Mauve: not visible. Also, mention in the legend the particular species that fall in the Attel., Anapl., and Betu. families</p>
    <p> p.11. </p>
    <p> - "We identify some limitations of MarkerScan." To avoid that users waste their time and resources, it would be desirable that MarkerScan performs a pre-scan to warn if the mentioned limitations will likely affect the results.</p>
    <p> p.12 </p>
    <p> - "lower memory...". Hardware and operating system requirements of MarkerScan should be clearly stated and compared in general terms with that of the other software mentioned here.</p>
    <p>Is the rationale for developing the new method (or application) clearly explained?</p>
    <p>Yes</p>
    <p>Is the description of the method technically sound?</p>
    <p>Yes</p>
    <p>Are the conclusions about the method and its performance adequately supported by the findings presented in the article?</p>
    <p>Yes</p>
    <p>If any results are presented, are all the source data underlying the results available to ensure full reproducibility?</p>
    <p>Yes</p>
    <p>Are sufficient details provided to allow replication of the method development and its use by others?</p>
    <p>Yes</p>
    <p>Reviewer Expertise:</p>
    <p>Eukaryotic genome evolution, comparative genomics.</p>
    <p>I confirm that I have read this submission and believe that I have an appropriate level of expertise to confirm that it is of an acceptable scientific standard, however I have significant reservations, as outlined above.</p>
  </body>
