    <p>Vancaester and Blaxter present a new software for dealing with mixed samples in genome sequencing projects. The paper is well-written with well-placed analyses provide sufficient proof that underscores the utility of the new software. I have only small suggestions that the Authors may consider when revising their MS.</p>
    <p> Possibly the largest concern is that MarkerScan searches at the family level only. Fixing the search at the family level has the risk of certain taxa not having any representatives from the same family in sequence databases. While this is unlikely to be a problem in metazoans or plants, in several protist groups it may be. Is there an easy fix around? If not this might need to be acknowledged.</p>
    <p> In the Results section, it would be helpful to potential readers to mention the run times of MarkerScan.</p>
